  "prompt": "Can we change marks of autonomous marksheet?",
  "response": "Changing marks on an autonomous marksheet is generally not permissible or ethical. Autonomously issued marksheets are official documents that reflect academic performance, and altering them can lead to serious consequences, including academic penalties or legal issues. \n\nIf you believe there is an error in your marks, the appropriate course of action is to contact the academic institution or body responsible for issuing the marksheet. They typically have a formal process for reviewing and rectifying any discrepancies in grades or marks. Always follow the official procedures to address such issues.",
